quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  7,73,"To the Thamud We sent their brother Salih. He said, \"O my people, worship God; you have no other god but Him. A veritable proof has come to you from your Lord: this is God's she-camel, a sign for you, so let her feed in God's land and do not harm her in any way, or you will be overwhelmed by a painful punishment"
  7,74,Remember when He made you successors to the 'Ad and settled you in the land. You built palaces on its plains and carved houses out of the mountains. Remember God's blessings and do not spread corruption in the land
  7,75,"but the arrogant leaders of his people said to the believers who were deemed weak, \"Do you know for certain that Salih is one sent from his Lord?\" They replied, \"We believe in the message which has been sent through him"
  7,76,"The arrogant leaders said, \"We reject what you believe in"
  7,77,"So they hamstrung the she-camel, and insolently defied the commandment of their Lord, saying, \"O Salih! Bring upon us what you threaten us with if you are indeed a messenger"
  7,78,"So the earthquake overwhelmed them, and morning found them prostrate in their dwelling places"
  7,79,"He left them, saying, \"My people, I delivered my Lord's messages to you and counselled you sincerely, but you do not like sincere advisors"
  7,80,"We sent Lot, who said to his people, \"How can you commit an abomination such as no one in the world has ever done before you"
  7,81,You lust after men rather than women! You transgress all bounds
  7,82,"The only answer given by his people was, \"Turn them out of your town. They are people who regard themselves to be pure"
  7,83,So We saved him and his family -- except for his wife. She was one of those who stayed behind
  7,84,"We rained down on them a shower [of brimstone]. Then see what was the end of the evil-doers"